 <!-- Deep dive -->
 <section class="border-b border-navy-800 bg-navy-950 py-20 sm:py-24">
 <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
 <span class="mb-3 inline-block font-mono text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-gold-500">The Buyer's Read</span>
 <h2 class="mb-8 font-heading text-3xl font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">
 Custom polos for Vegas service crews and customer-facing staff.
 </h2>

 <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-navy-200">
 <p>
 Custom polo shirts with an embroidered chest logo are the default uniform for service technicians, account managers, sales reps, and any role where employees are seen by customers, vendors, or the public. The visual signal needs to read as established business — not team event — and embroidery on a pique-knit polo carries that weight in a way a screen-printed t-shirt never will.
 </p>
 <p>
 The blank decision usually splits along Vegas-summer lines. For year-round service work in conditioned spaces (HVAC inside calls, electrical inside fit-outs, plumbing residential), the Port Authority K500 Silk Touch in cotton-poly is the workhorse — it embroiders cleanly, comes in 30-plus colors S through 6XL, and survives a long laundering cycle. For outdoor service work in the May–September Vegas heat, swap to the K540 Performance polyester or the Sport-Tek ST650; both wick sweat fast enough to keep shirts presentable through a 110°F afternoon.
 </p>
 <p>
 Name embroidery has become the new standard for customer-facing trades. Standard layout is company logo on the left chest at 3.5 inches wide, and first name + last initial on the right chest at half-inch lettering. The cost adds a small per-piece premium, the production time adds about a day, and the trust signal is real — homeowners and facility managers are measurably more comfortable letting a named technician into the building than an anonymous one.
 </p>
 <p>
 For a long-running program, we set up a private company store with your blanks, decoration spec, and employee size profiles preloaded. Reorders run at the same per-piece pricing as the initial order, new hires get fully-decorated polos when they start without your HR team chasing approvals, and per-employee allowances can match your existing apparel budget. See <a href="/company-stores/" class="text-gold-400 underline decoration-gold-500/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-500">how the company store program works</a> for the operational details.
 </p>
 <p>
 For deeper reads on polos and embroidery, see our <a href="/blog/custom-polo-shirts-las-vegas/" class="text-gold-400 underline decoration-gold-500/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-500">custom polo shirts buyer's guide</a>, the <a href="/blog/port-authority-polos-vs-alternatives/" class="text-gold-400 underline decoration-gold-500/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-500">Port Authority vs alternatives comparison</a>, and the <a href="/blog/how-much-to-embroider-a-polo/" class="text-gold-400 underline decoration-gold-500/30 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-gold-500">embroidery cost breakdown</a>.
 </p>
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- FAQ -->
 <section class="border-b border-navy-800 bg-navy-900/30 py-20 sm:py-24">
 <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
 <span class="mb-3 inline-block font-mono text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-[0.25em] text-gold-500">FAQ</span>
 <h2 class="mb-12 font-heading text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight sm:text-4xl">Polo questions, answered.</h2>

 <div class="space-y-3">
 {faqs.map((f) => (
 <details class="group rounded-xl border border-navy-700/40 bg-navy-900/40 p-5 transition-all hover:border-gold-500/30 open:border-gold-500/40">
 <summary class="flex cursor-pointer list-none items-start justify-between gap-4">
 <h3 class="font-heading text-lg font-bold leading-tight tracking-tight text-white">{f.q}</h3>
 <span class="mt-1 flex-shrink-0 text-gold-500 transition-transform group-open:rotate-45">
 <svg class="h-5 w-5" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M12 4v16m8-8H4"/></svg>
 </span>
 </summary>
 <p class="mt-4 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-300">{f.a}</p>
 </details>
 ))}
 </div>
 </div>
 </section>

 <!-- Related -->
 <section class="border-b border-navy-800 bg-navy-950 py-16">
